        <!-- ═══ USAGE TAB ═══ -->
        <div class="tab-content" id="tab-usage" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">

          <!-- When and Where to Use -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When and Where to Use</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">The Split Button combines a primary action with secondary options accessible via a dropdown chevron.</p>

            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-top: 24px;">
              <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; transition: all 0.25s ease;">
                <h3 id="when-to-use-details" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                  <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
                  When to use
                </h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">For a primary action that has related secondary options (e.g., "Save" + "Save As...", "Save &amp; Close").</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Compound actions in toolbars where space is constrained and secondary options need to be grouped.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">Form submissions with variants (e.g., "Submit" + "Submit &amp; New", "Submit &amp; Close").</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; transition: all 0.25s ease;">
                <h3 id="when-not-to-use" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                  <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#e42527" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
                  When NOT to use
                </h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">When there is no secondary action needed -- use a standard Primary button.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">For navigation actions -- buttons should trigger actions, not page transitions.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">For a single simple action where no dropdown is warranted.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Detailed Do's and Don'ts -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Complete Do's and Don'ts</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Visual and interaction guidelines to ensure Split Buttons are effective, scalable, and accessible.</p>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Pair with dropdown:</strong> Always pair with an Action Dropdown or menu that opens from the Chevron Part.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Concise labels:</strong> Keep the primary action label to 1-2 words for clarity.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Use prefix icon:</strong> Reinforce the primary action meaning (e.g., "+" for create/add).</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Consistent placement:</strong> Position where you would normally place a Primary button.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Primary action visible:</strong> The most common action should always be the button label, not hidden behind the chevron.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>No secondary action:</strong> Don't use when there is no secondary action -- use a standard Primary button.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>One per view:</strong> Don't use more than one Split Button per view/section.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Not for navigation:</strong> Don't use for navigation actions.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Critical actions:</strong> Don't hide the only/critical action behind the chevron.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Loading + dropdown:</strong> Don't use the Loading state without disabling the dropdown interaction.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Button mixing:</strong> Don't mix with other Primary-styled buttons in the same group.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Key Differences from Standard Button -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="key-differences" class="doc-section-title">Key Differences from Standard Button</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Understanding how Split Button behavior differs from the standard Button component.</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Two distinct interactive zones:</strong> The Split Button has two separate clickable areas (Button Part + Chevron Part), unlike the standard Button which is a single target.</li>
              <li><strong>Icons always visible:</strong> Both prefix and suffix icons are always shown -- there is no boolean toggle to hide them like in the standard Button.</li>
              <li><strong>Divider is structural:</strong> The divider between parts is a structural element that separates the two interaction zones, not a decorative element.</li>
              <li><strong>Focus wraps entire component:</strong> The Focus state wraps the entire component with an outer ring (12px radius), unlike the standard button which wraps just the single button area.</li>
              <li><strong>Loading replaces entire content:</strong> The Loading state replaces both parts with a spinner, not just the label text.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

