            <h2 id="figma-usage" class="doc-section-title">Figma Usage</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">How to find and configure the Split Button in Figma.</p>
            <style>
              .cp-code-area { background: #0a0a0c; padding: 24px; overflow-x: auto; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: #e2e8f0; border-radius: 12px; }
            </style>
            <div class="cp-code-area" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
Component Set: Button<br>
Node ID: 15897:18750<br>
File: UEMS - Design System 3.0<br>
<br>
Example variant string:<br>
Variant=Primary Split, Size=Large, State=Default, RTL=False
            </div>

            <h3 id="instance-overrides" class="doc-h3">Instance Overrides</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Select the split button instance in your Figma file.</li>
              <li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Change <strong>Size</strong> to match layout requirements (Large, Medium, Small, Xsmall).</li>
              <li><strong>Step 3:</strong> Swap <strong>Prefix Icon</strong> to the appropriate action icon (e.g., add, save, download).</li>
              <li><strong>Step 4:</strong> Edit the <strong>Label</strong> text to match the primary action.</li>
              <li><strong>Step 5:</strong> The <strong>Suffix Icon</strong> (chevron) should generally remain as the default chevron-down.</li>
            </ul>
